M51 was recorded by Lord Rosse in 1845.
Lord Rosseâ€™s 72-inch telescope enabled him to see the spiral shape of the M51 nebula. Like many astronomers, he drew the bright parts of the image with a dark pencil, making his drawing look like a photographic negative.
